After having gone to Tacos El Bronco for a while, I figured I'd try here since it's a little closer to my place. Similar to Tacos El Bronco, I really like the food here, and the staff is really nice; the quality of the tacos is pretty much the same, as are the offerings.  But it takes a long time to get a taco. Or any food for that matter. Perhaps their delivery is really popular, or perhaps I really just end up going at the wrong time every time I come in, but 25+ minutes for a few takeout tacos in an otherwise empty dining room is a bit much to ask.  I wouldn't mind coming back here at all, because the food is nice, but I'd have to have forgotten about the amount of time it takes.

When I got my delivery using UberEats, I was missing my Torta Cubana, so I called the restaurant. They told me it will take 15 minutes. I called them again after 20 minutes later to make sure that to tell the delivery person know where I work is tricky to find, but the lady repeated herself that it'll take 15 minutes to arrive and rudely hung up on me. I've waited for 2 hours and I called them again to tell them not to deliver it if they haven't done so. The first call, they never picked up, so I immediately called them again and someone did pick up, but I'm assuming they're on mute because I did not hear anything. After 10 seconds of silence, they hung up. No words to explain how impolite they are.
